# Musubi project rules (Cursor)

The canonical working agreement for coding agents on this project lives at [CLAUDE.md](mdc:../../CLAUDE.md) in the repo root. Read it before any meaningful edit.

Also read:

- [AGENTS.md](mdc:../../AGENTS.md) — condensed version for all agent tools.
- [docs/AGENT-PROCESS.md](mdc:../../docs/AGENT-PROCESS.md) — multi-agent concurrency model.
- [docs/architecture/00-index/agent-guardrails.md](mdc:../../docs/architecture/00-index/agent-guardrails.md) — the four non-negotiables.

## Top rules (don't forget)

1. **Stay inside the slice's `owns_paths`.** Read anywhere; write only there. Every slice is described at `docs/architecture/_slices/slice-<id>.md`.
2. **Tests first.** The first commit on your branch is the test file derived from the spec's Test Contract.
3. **API surface is frozen per version.** Don't touch `src/musubi/api/`, `openapi.yaml`, or `proto/` unless your slice is `slice-api-*`.
4. **Types are owned by `slice-types`.** Don't touch `src/musubi/types/` unless your slice is that one.
5. **Conventional Commits.** `feat(scope): ...`, `test(scope): ...`, `docs(scope): ...`. Same-PR spec changes get a `spec-update: <doc-path>` trailer.
6. **`make check` must pass** before you open a PR.

## File patterns to remember

- `src/musubi/<module>/` → implementation.
- `tests/<module>/` mirrors it.
- `docs/architecture/<NN-section>/<topic>.md` → specs.
- `docs/architecture/_slices/slice-<id>.md` → your work order.
- `docs/architecture/13-decisions/NNNN-<slug>.md` → ADRs.

## Tool-use gotchas specific to Cursor

- Cursor's auto-apply can easily drift outside `owns_paths` when following suggestions across files. Keep a mental map of your slice's allowed paths and reject cross-slice edits into `forbidden_paths`.
- When Cursor offers to "fix all" across the repo, confirm the scope is inside your slice — don't rubber-stamp a sweeping refactor in a slice PR.
